Consider the following JSP code and trace the execution. Identify all implicit objects used and their scopes:
<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html" %>
<%
 String name = request.getParameter("username");
 session.setAttribute("user", name);
 application.setAttribute("visitors", 500);
 int count = (Integer) pageContext.getAttribute("counter");
 counter++;
 pageContext.setAttribute("counter", counter);
%>
Welcome <%= name %>! Visitor #<%= counter %>

Given the following servlet code, identify all thread-safety issues and suggest fixes:
public class MyServlet extends HttpServlet {
 private int counter; // Line 1
 private String userData; // Line 2

 protected void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException {
 String input = request.getParameter("data"); // Line 3
 userData = input; // Line 4
 counter++; // Line 5
 response.getWriter().write("Count: " + counter + ", Data: " + userData);
 }
}
